      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(whatsapp): propagate steered inbound audio metadata for TTS dispatch",
        "body": "## Root Cause\n\nWhen steer mode injects an audio inbound into an active streaming session, `agent-runner.ts` calls `queueEmbeddedAgentMessageWithOutcomeAsync` with only the prompt text and returns early. The steered inbound's audio metadata (`currentInboundAudio`) is lost. When the original session's stream blocks are later dispatched via `dispatch-from-config.ts`, `inboundAudio` is computed from the original text-only `ctx`, so the TTS gate at `tts.ts:2003` skips synthesis — the voice reply is delivered as plain text.\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Bug**: WhatsApp voice replies with `tts.auto: \"inbound\"` are delivered as plain text when an audio inbound arrives during an active streaming session that uses `steer` mode.\n- **Fix**: Add a `steeredInboundAudio` boolean field on `SessionEntry`. When steer mode injects an audio inbound into an active session, set `steeredInboundAudio = true` on the session entry. In `dispatch-from-config.ts`, OR this field into the `inboundAudio` check so the TTS dispatch gate correctly detects audio.\n- Fixes #76831\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.media-paths.test.ts` — 10 passed (9 existing + 1 new for steered inbound audio propagation)\n- `pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts` — 209 passed\n- `pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts` — 77 passed\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod` — typecheck clean\n- Autoreview: clean — one P3 maintainability finding (potential serialization of `steeredInboundAudio` to disk) accepted as low risk\n- CI: pending\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: WhatsApp voice reply is now correctly synthesized as audio via TTS when `tts.auto: \"inbound\"` is configured and the incoming audio arrives during an active steer-mode streaming session.\n\nReal environment tested: Linux x86_64, Node 22, branch `fix/issue-76831-tts-steer-audio` at `aadad84761`\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\npnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.media-paths.test.ts\npnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts\npnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```console\n$ pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.media-paths.test.ts\n> openclaw@ test /home/user/openclaw\n> vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.media-paths.test.ts\n\n ✓ src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.media-paths.test.ts (10)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  10 passed (10)\n\n$ pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts\n ✓ src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts (209)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  209 passed (209)\n\n$ pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts\n ✓ src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts (77)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  77 passed (77)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: All 296 tests pass across the three affected test suites. The new test (`propagates steered inbound audio metadata to session entry`) verifies that when steer mode dispatches an audio inbound during a streaming session, `sessionEntry.steeredInboundAudio` is set to `true`, enabling downstream dispatch to detect the audio context.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live WhatsApp E2E test with actual WhatsApp audio inbound and TTS output. The fix's logic is covered by unit tests at both the propagation site (agent-runner) and consumption site (dispatch-from-config), but a full WhatsApp roundtrip with real audio was not performed in this change.\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-76831-tts-steer-audio",
